snippet: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo wants to win as many votes as possible in the election on Tuesday, but some liberals suspect he also wants to weaken a political party.
abstract: New York Gov Andrew M Cuomo wants to win as many votes as possible in upcoming election, but some liberals think he also wants to weaken the Working Families Party; WFP agreed to endorse Cuomo after he promised to push for a number of its goals, but Cuomo has been promoting his own political party, Women's Equality Party, on whose ballot line he will also appear.
lead_paragraph: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo wants to win as many votes as possible in the election on Tuesday, but some liberals suspect he also wants to weaken a political party.

headline.main: Cuomo, Backed by Working Families Party, May Chip Away at Its Clout at the Polls
headline.print_headline: Cuomo, Backed by Working Families Party, May Erode Its Clout at the Polls
